{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04334/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04334"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:43:34"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, pan, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man fixes a model's outfit in a dressing room."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04334/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04334","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04334/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04334"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04334/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04334/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04334/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04334/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04334/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04334/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04334/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04334/canvas/1/a3547727-6653-44c2-ae1a-4eef2954d46f","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:59:31.714Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Some critics have argued that <em>Phantom Thread </em>champions a view of fashion (that is, of art) that can only be crafted out of intensity and oppression (Zacharek, “'Phantom Thread'”). However, to view the film in this way, as Adam Nayman argues, is to miss how it critiques Reynolds’s behaviors: “If Reynolds’s empire is defined by oppression and anxiety—the flip side of its serene, focused workflow—it’s because these are the inherent vices of its proprietors; to think that the movie ascribes the real virtue is a misreading. If the hypnotic monotony of the House of Woodcock, synced to Greenwood’s coruscating score induces a trance state, it’s a morbid sort of daydream—a perfumed labyrinth” (Nayman, <em>Masterworks</em>, 213).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04334/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:457.38896366083446,174.99327052489912,1011.6823687752355,706.7563930013458"}}}]}]}]}